President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to Abu Dhabi, United Arab Emirates, to pay respects upon the death of His Highness Sheikh Khalifa bin Zayed Al Nahyan, President of the United Arab Emirates, on May 16, 2022. The delegation will be led by Vice President Kamala Harris. Other members of the delegation include Mr. Sean Murphy, Chargé d’Affaires ad interim, U.S. Embassy Abu Dhabi, Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken, Secretary of Defense Lloyd J. Austin III, Special Presidential Envoy for Climate John F. Kerry, Assistant to the President and National Security Advisor to the Vice President Philip Gordon, Director of the Central Intelligence Agency William Burns, Deputy Assistant to the President and Coordinator for the Middle East and North Africa Brett McGurk, and Special Assistant to the President and Senior Director for the Middle East and North Africa Barbara Leaf.